title: Indonesia’s Widodo Considers Cutting Fuel Prices
text:
JAKARTA, Indonesia—Indonesian President Joko Widodo said he is looking for ways to cut fuel prices to help consumers, setting up a possible clash between the government and state-owned oil and gas giant Pertamina, which says prices are already below market value.
